(Corrects to show block is onshore in first paragraph.)  Kosmos Energy Ltd.â€™s unit in
Cameroon signed a deal with the state-owned National
Hydrocarbons Corp. to spend $18 million exploring for oil in the
onshore Fako block, according to a statement from the two
companies.  Kosmos will conduct a six-year study of the 1,289 square-
kilometer area, including collecting data and drilling two
exploration wells, according to the statement, which was handed
to reporters in Yaounde, the capital, today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
